title: Jane Hume announces deputy leadership bid | 7NEWS
description: Liberal Senator Jane Hume announces her candidacy for deputy leader of the Liberal Party, citing the need for change as the party's primary vote has declined since the last election. Health Minister Mark Butler questions Taylor's qualifications, pointing to his record as energy minister and shadow treasurer. title: Cooper Woods claims Australia's first gold at 2026 Winter Olympics | 7NEWS
description: Australian mogul skier Cooper Woods has won gold at the 2026 Winter Olympics in Milano e Cortina, delivering the best run of his career in the superfinals despite not being favoured to win. Woods, known for his heroic rescue of a young friend named Amalia from a 10-metre waterfall when he was 12 years old, was watched by that same friend during his gold medal performance. His uncle and former coach Peter Topalovic describes the victory as an incredible achievement for the young athlete who has won the hearts of the winter sports community. title: South East Queensland braces for 400mm deluge | 7NEWS
description: South East Queensland is forecast to receive up to 400 millimetres of rainfall extending into the weekend, with Brisbane and the Gold Coast expected to be hardest hit by the summer deluge. The region faces potential severe thunderstorms and flash flooding warnings, with today identified as the peak impact day. Three-day rainfall totals could reach mid-200s to 300 millimetres in some areas, while northern New South Wales locations like Byron Bay and Coffs Harbour are expected to receive 100 to 140 millimetres. title: Angus Taylor wins Liberal leadership spill as Sussan Ley ousted | 7NEWS
description: Angus Taylor has been elected leader of the Liberal Party of Australia, defeating Susan Ley 34 votes to 17 in a spill motion ballot. title: Sussan Ley resigns as Liberal leader after nine months | 7NEWS
description: Sussan Ley resigns as leader of the Liberal Party after nine months, following a party room vote that saw Angus Taylor elected as her replacement. The member for Farrer, who has represented her New South Wales electorate for 25 years since winning by 206 votes in 2001, announces she will resign from Parliament entirely within weeks. Ley reflects on her leadership achievements including establishing a Royal Commission into anti-Semitism and landing an energy policy, while expressing gratitude to supporters and calling for clear air for the incoming leader. title: Sussan Ley to resign from politics after being ousted as Liberal Party Leader
description: Sussan Ley has announced she will permanently step back from politics after being voted out as Liberal party leader in a party room vote on Friday morning. Ley was defeated by Angus Taylor in a 34-17 vote of Liberal Party MPs at 9am.
